LOOK FOR THE LIGHT 
———————————————————————
I’ve been looking for a @thelastofus billboard for the last month. Today… on the day… driving home from getting food with @lionnessdreads I let out an almighty noise while pulling on to the curb. Which was met with “WHAT’S WRONG?!” Then “I thought you were having a heart attack!” There it was… my favourite game, made in to a series, and plastered on a billboard in my town. I wanted a picture of myself next to one since it was announced. I looked like crap but this was the moment. The visible joy in my face, creating content at the side of the road as people drive past. The old me never would, I used to be so self conscious about making content in public. We stood and looked at it for a while, and talked. Vanessa actually got a bit emotional and said it meant so much to her to see me so happy. It’s literally just some paper on a wall. But man it was glorious. We even tore off a small piece to keep. Technically TLOU merchandise 😂 I hope everyone has enjoyed the first episode. I’m going to watch right now! 
———————————————————————

📺 ON THE BIG SCREEN 📺 
———————————————————————
What is your favourite TV/Film adaptation of a video game?
Video games to film have been a constant throughout the years, and are either a major flop or a giant hit. When something flops hard it has the potential to destroy a franchise by not only failing to bring in new fans but also alienating the original ones. The Last of Us faced a lot of backlash and controversy throughout its development due to die hard fans not being happy. Now it’s here I’ve seen very few people who are unhappy with it. I keep seeing these billboards everywhere now! Which brings me great joy. I literally pull up the car at each one and get out to make content 😂

2 YEARS
———————————————————————
2 years ago today I posted about the The Last of Us PS5 I had made. Little did I know in that moment what impact that it would have on my life. 2 years later and I’m still so overrun with making them that I haven’t made anything else in such a long time. From the moment this went live I admit I was somewhat consumed by its success to an unhealthy degree. It took a long time for me to step out from underneath it to find myself again. But I’m not complaining, TLOU has made such big changes to my life in so many ways. I am eternally grateful to the success and opportunities it has brought me.

🛑 LOOK FOR THE LIGHT 🛑 
———————————————————————
What did everyone think of Left Behind?
Obviously for the most part it was quite true to the game, and for us gamers we understood everything that was going on. But I heard from other friends and family that they weren’t really aware of what was going on fully. The introduction and departure of Riley who had barely been named at this point to a fully dedicated episode to what happened some months before. I felt like maybe more effort should have been made to fill in some blanks for those who haven’t played the game as it was maybe a little too ambiguous. This episode was definitely for the gamers; and unfortunately scored the lowest so far in such a strong series. Don’t get me wrong I enjoyed it and is a huge part of the story. But it seems like the average Joe is struggling to keep up with some of the plot at this point. I’m hoping next weeks episode is going to be action packed with our first encounter with David and his men. 
———————————————————————

📼 HAPPY BIRTHDAY 📼 
———————————————————————
Now The Last of Us series has finished we can take time to reflect on it. It got a lot of hate, from casting choices to “woke filler” all in all… I feel like they did an amazing job, I do have criticisms myself but I really enjoyed the series and am just very happy that a game we all love so much got brought to the masses in such a beautiful way. Season 2, Factions 2 and TLOU III will be here before we know it. In the mean time enjoy a batch of Joel’s tapes I’ve been working on recently. All ready to go to new homes.

🌿 ENDURE AND SURVIVE 🌿
———————————————————————
Little life update. I’ve been rather quiet recently content wise. For those who have been paying attention, the past 6 months have been really hard and I’ve not really had anywhere to live, never mind actually make content. ⚔️ Valhalla ⚔️ 
———————————————————————
For the last few years I got in to a really bad habit of only playing games when I was filming. Everything was for content. Which on one level is awesome, but I wasn’t gaming for fun anymore. I couldn’t just kick back and chill, play some games at leisure and have fun. Everything was always on, always narrating, always progressing the story. Minimal side quests and exploring. It got to the point where I didn’t even know how to play for fun anymore. Recently I’ve had some free time and started falling in love with playing again. I started AC Valhalla on the day it came out, and it’s still unfinished because I only played it while I was filming. I’m finally playing it again and loving it. Riding around, playing a bit of story, some side quests, some puzzles and collectibles. AC games are ones I absolutely love to 100% so I’m in my element. It feels good to actually play again. 🖤⚔️

🖤 THE LAST OF US 🖤
———————————————————————
Today is a good day. Recently I’ve been able to play more games, which has been great for me. I got Part I on the day it came out. The only video game I’ve bought for myself in the last year. But I’ve not had the time or facilities to play.
The Last of Us has always had a special place in my heart. @lionnessdreads has always been supportive and welcoming to my love for TLOU. So much that she got a firefly tattoo on her thumb as a mark of her love. She sat by my side as we watched the HBO series and enjoyed it so much asked if we could play the game after. A perfect opportunity to dive in to Part I. Showing someone your favourite game for the first time is special, and even more so to watch them fall in love with the characters the way you have. Today we finished the game and it was such a good feeling. We sat and talked about the story and the characters after while the Home Screen played in the background. Then she said something that every boyfriend wants to hear from their girl… 
“Can we play Part II..?”
It’s been two years, that I’ve not been ready to play it again, but now after all this time, I have healed, I have grown. 
I’m ready to live it again and share it. 
We even decided to mark the occasion with some content. A little different than my usual but it matched the vibe perfectly.

🌿 REMASTERED 🌿

Folks have been waiting for me to chime in about the TLOU Part II Remaster announcement. I am absolutely thrilled, but I am biased so I would be… Not everyone shares my enthusiasm for a remaster of a pretty new and already graphically perfect game and I get that. Everyone wants Factions II and Part III… Why release Part II again on next gen when it doesn’t have much more to offer than it already had. They did the same thing back in 2013-14, original game was released on PS3 back in 2013, end of the PS3 era, a year later it gets remaster for PS4 with a couple of added extras. Even if you want to be blunt about it and call it a cash grab. TLOU is in its peak right now. With more fans than ever due to the HBO series, these new fans are being converted in to gamers who are picking up, any or all of the previous incarnations. If anything this will prove to ND how popular the game is and push them forward with DLC, Factions II and Part III. I can’t wait and will be getting my hands on the WLF Edition.

TOMORROW 

So tomorrow is a big day. The Last of Us Part II Remastered is up for preorder. Including the amazing WLF Edition, and for worldwide release too. I’m glad lessons were learnt from last time. Now for most this won’t be a big deal and even for those who do care about it. For me, this means so much more. When the Firefly Edition was released I really wanted it, but literally had nothing at that point in my life. The only reason I own this edition was because a good friend of mine gifted it to me. Fast toward to today. A lot of hard work, love and support later, I am in a position where I am capable of and absolutely looking forward to preordering the WLF edition tomorrow. 
I am so proud to see how far we’ve come in such a short amount of time.
